		    <title class="- topic/title ">
			      <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">47.000</ph> Scope of part.</title>
		    <conbody class="- topic/body concept/conbody ">
			      <ol id="d2711e13" class="- topic/ol ">
				        <li class="- topic/li ">
					          <p id="d2725e17" class="- topic/p ">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(a)</ph>
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
						            This part prescribes policies and procedures for-</p>
					          <ol id="d2711e23" class="- topic/ol ">
						            <li class="- topic/li ">
							              <p id="d2725e27" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(1)</ph>
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
								                Applying transportation and traffic management considerations in the acquisition of supplies; and</p>
						            </li>
						            <li class="- topic/li ">
							              <p id="d2725e36" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(2)</ph>
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
								                Acquiring transportation or transportation-related services by contract methods other than bills of lading, transportation requests, transportation warrants, and similar transportation forms. Transportation and transportation services can be obtained by acquisition subject to the FAR or by acquisition under <xref href="http://uscode.house.gov/browse.xhtml;jsessionid=114A3287C7B3359E597506A31FC855B3"
                              scope="external"
                              format="html"
                              class="- topic/xref ">49 U.S.C. 10721</xref> or <xref href="http://uscode.house.gov/browse.xhtml;jsessionid=114A3287C7B3359E597506A31FC855B3"
                              scope="external"
                              format="html"
                              class="- topic/xref ">49 U.S.C. 13712</xref>. Even though the FAR does not regulate the acquisition of transportation or transportation-related services when the bill of lading is the contract, this contract method is widely used and, therefore, relevant guidance on the use of the bill of lading is provided in this part (see <xref href="FAR-i1071359.dita#i1071359"
                              base="i1071359"
                              outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                              class="- topic/xref ">47.104</xref>).</p>
						            </li>
					          </ol>
				        </li>
				        <li class="- topic/li ">
					          <p id="d2725e56" class="- topic/p ">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(b)</ph>
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
						            The definitions in this part have been condensed from statutory definitions. In case of inconsistency between the language of this part and the statutory requirements, the statute shall prevail.</p>
				        </li>
